Package: OptiSparseMET
Type: Package
Title: Sparse Multi-Environment Trial Design with Flexible Local Field Layout
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person(
      given   = "Felicien",
      family  = "Akohoue",
      email   = "akohoue.f@gmail.com",
      role    = c("aut", "cre"),
      comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-2160-0182")
    )
Description: Constructs sparse multi-environment trial (MET) designs by
    jointly addressing across-environment treatment allocation and
    within-environment field layout under shared statistical, genetic, and
    logistical constraints. Allocation supports two strategies: a
    random-balanced (M3-inspired) approach that guarantees full treatment
    coverage while tolerating unequal environment sizes, and a balanced
    incomplete block design (BIBD, M4) approach that enforces equal
    replication across environments (Montesinos-Lopez et al. 2023
    <doi:10.1002/tpg2.20305>). Optional common treatments establish
    cross-environment genetic connectivity. Structure-aware allocation is
    available via family labels or groups derived from genomic or pedigree
    relationship matrices. Feasibility helpers verify per-environment
    capacity before allocation begins. Seed-constrained replication plans
    account for available seed quantities. Within-environment layouts are
    built for repeated-check augmented, partially replicated (p-rep), and
    RCBD-type block designs, or for fixed-grid alpha row-column stream
    designs. Both constructors support optional grouping from family labels
    or relationship matrices, optional genetic dispersion optimisation, and
    mixed-model efficiency evaluation under A-optimality, D-optimality, and
    CDmean criteria for genomic selection (Rincent et al. 2012
    <doi:10.1534/genetics.112.141473>). Design optimisation is available
    via random restart, simulated annealing, and genetic algorithm methods.
    An end-to-end pipeline coordinates allocation, seed feasibility checks,
    local field design construction, and assembly of a unified MET field book.
